Several notes even for me:
1. This bug **does not** happen when directive `cython: infer_types = True` is set. I understand that majority of users does not set this directive though...
2. I think we can discuss with the note:
   > I'm not completely convinced that `list[cython.int]` is a sensible thing to support

   @da-woods what do you propose to happen when user provides C-type as attribute to the list? A warning?
3. I created a matrix to understand what C code is under which circumstances generated:
   **TL;DR**: It seems that the best approach is to use proposed change in https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/7729#issuecomment-4583205293 but with a twist that we allow inferring pyobject (it will allow to optimise expreassion usage like `l[0].bar()`). In this case the only C code that will be "worse" is the case of `list[cython.int]` with `infer_type` directive enabled which is the case we can live with...

